From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921: guard testmode against NULL drv_own
 on USB

The mt7921_tm_set() function calls __mt792x_mcu_drv_pmctrl(dev) which
expands to (dev)->hif_ops->drv_own(dev). On USB, the hif_ops struct
does not set .drv_own or .fw_own (both remain NULL) because power
management ownership transfer is not needed for USB devices — PM is
intentionally disabled for USB at init time.

However, testmode is registered unconditionally for all bus types. When
a testmode command is issued on a USB-attached MT7921 device, the call
chain reaches __mt792x_mcu_drv_pmctrl(dev) which dereferences the NULL
function pointer, causing an immediate kernel NULL pointer dereference
panic.

Add a NULL check before calling __mt792x_mcu_drv_pmctrl(). If drv_own
is not implemented for the current bus (i.e., USB), return -EOPNOTSUPP
with proper mutex release, since testmode requires full power management
control which USB does not provide.

This is consistent with how other PM-related paths handle USB: the
init code explicitly disables PM for USB devices (pm.enable = false)
and the PCIe-specific drv_own/fw_own functions are never registered
for USB.

Predicted crash signature (unpatched):
  BUG: kernel NULL pointer dereference, address: 0000000000000000
  RIP: 0010:0x0
  Call Trace:
   mt7921_tm_set+0xXX/0xXXX [mt7921u]
   mt7921_testmode_cmd+0xXX/0xXXX [mt7921u]

Fixes: bf32e8629f7d ("mt76: mt7921: add testmode support")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/testmode.c | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/testmode.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/testmode.c
index 1234567..abcdef1 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/testmode.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/testmode.c
@@ -57,7 +57,12 @@ mt7921_tm_set(struct mt792x_dev *dev, struct mt7921_tm_cmd *req)
 	if (testmode) {
 		/* Make sure testmode running on full power mode */
 		pm->enable = false;
 		cancel_delayed_work_sync(&pm->ps_work);
 		cancel_work_sync(&pm->wake_work);
-		__mt792x_mcu_drv_pmctrl(dev);
+		if (dev->hif_ops->drv_own) {
+			__mt792x_mcu_drv_pmctrl(dev);
+		} else {
+			ret = -EOPNOTSUPP;
+			goto out;
+		}
+
 		phy->test.state = MT76_TM_STATE_ON;
 	}

